In the limit ξ f 0, the dynamical variable Nˆ ({ri}, V) is the actual number of water molecules in the volume V. However, for ﬁnite ξ, Nˆ ({ri}, V) is a continuous and differentiable function of {ri}. We construct the biasing potential with this variable. In particular, we let

