(45) Before integrating the joint distribution, PV(N, N˜ ), it is important to ensure that the conditional probability distribution, PV(N˜ |N), has been sampled adequately for the entire range of relevant N˜ values. Failure to do so can result in signiﬁcant errors in PV(N). We have circumvented this problem by choosing a small value of ξ ) 0.1 Å, so that N˜ closely follows N.
