(47) The data for thin and cubic volumes end at different values of the reduced ﬂuctuation because their standard deviations, (〈(δN)2〉V)1/2, differ by 18% despite the fact that their distributions have the same mean, 〈N〉V ) FV. This difference reﬂects that 〈(δN)2〉V ) FV + F2∫V dr∫V dr′[g(|r- r′|)1], where the bulk solvent radial distribution function, g(r), oscillates about its asymptotic value of 1.
